Package: robotstxtr
Type: Package
Title: Faithful 'robots.txt' Parsing Using Google's Matcher Algorithm
Version: 0.1.0
Language: en-US
Authors@R:
    person("Bart", "Turczynski", email = "bartek@turczynski.pl", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-8788-7980"))
Description: Evaluates whether URLs may be crawled according to 'robots.txt'
    rules, using a vendored, upstream-test-validated snapshot of Google's
    open-source C++ 'robots.txt' matcher so that allow and disallow decisions
    match Googlebot behavior. Fetches 'robots.txt' documents with a
    deterministic, conservative policy built on 'httr2', constructs fetch
    origins with 'rurl', and returns richly typed, vectorized decisions with
    per-rule match metadata. All network access in tests, examples, and
    vignettes is mocked or served locally, so no internet connection is
    required to install, test, or check the package. The bundled matcher
    derives from Google's 'robotstxt' project
    <https://github.com/google/robotstxt>, distributed under the Apache License
    2.0; see the package NOTICE.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
